      <h2 id="ka-rubric">DAMA KA rubric — Data Quality Management</h2>
      <p>
        Per <a href="/resource?path=docs/adr/0001-adopt-dcam-dmbok-elements.md">ADR 0001</a> Wave 1, KA-tagged pages carry a consistent rubric — <strong>Purpose · Activities · Deliverables · Roles · Metrics · Maturity</strong>. The summaries below map each rubric section onto the detail above; like the rest of this page they are a first-cut provisional draft for <em>Compliance &amp; Risk WG</em> ratification.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          Give OPDA, member firms, and the consumers and regulators who rely on PDTF claims a shared way to talk
          about <em>how good</em> a claim is — across six dimensions — separate from how strongly it is attested,
          anchored on <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/eur/2016/679/article/5">UK GDPR Art 5(1)(d)</a>
          accuracy (see <a href="#overview">§1 Overview</a>).
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Activities</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Define the six DQ dimensions per claim type per Assurance Level (<a href="#dimensions">§2</a>).</li>
          <li>Author per-claim-type measurement protocols (<a href="#measurement">§3</a>).</li>
          <li>Set the AL × DQ floors (<a href="#al-mapping">§4</a>) and validate quarterly submissions.</li>
          <li>Spot-check sampled scores and flag inflated ratings (<a href="#reporting">§5</a>).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Deliverables</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>This published framework, plus the per-claim-type measurement-protocol matrix (<a href="#protocol-shape">§3.1</a>).</li>
          <li>A per-firm, per-dimension DQ profile fed quarterly into the <a href="/governance/accreditation-directory">Accreditation Directory</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Roles</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Compliance &amp; Risk WG</strong> — owns the framework end to end (<a href="#governance">§6</a>).</li>
          <li><strong>Technical WG</strong> — schema hooks and per-overlay validation rules.</li>
          <li><strong>Domain Data Stewards</strong> — context-specific measurement protocols.</li>
          <li><strong>Member firms</strong> — quarterly self-attestation and evidence retention.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Metrics</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>% of accredited firms submitting quarterly DQ profiles on time.</li>
          <li>Median DQ score per dimension across the Directory.</li>
          <li>Audit-trail-flagged score adjustments per quarter.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Maturity</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Gap</strong> today — the framework is drafted but awaits C&amp;R WG kick-off. Reaches
          <strong>Established</strong> once it is ratified and the first quarterly DQ profiles land in the
          Accreditation Directory, and <strong>Strong</strong> once independent audit attestations cover ≥ 3
          dimensions for a majority of accredited firms.
        </p>
      </section>
